<font color="#FF0000">MISSING IN ACTION</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb  7 13:10:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I empathize with those who's loved ones disappeared in that quagmire which is still significant in our collective American history.  I visited North Vietnam in 1991 and 1994. <br>
In both cases I was astounded by the warmth of the Vietnamese people and their curiosity about Americans.  I became friends with university professors, artists, doctors and ordinary people.  <br><br>
Inside myself, I have wounds that never healed from a very confusing time in that period of world history...Vietnam.  That is why I visited Vietnam.  While like all of you I suffer my own pain about those who we lost and those who never returned from the war, you must also know there were nearly a million Vietnamese who were lost in that war as well. They deserve recognition just as our POW/MIAs do.
